@node "Intr" "Introduction"
Forever ago I wanted an email door for ?Express. Nothing was  out
there  aside  from  a custom door by RRR. This wasn't public so I
started on this little effort.

Original MoMail used some godforsaken programming to allow a  BBS
to  have  'unlimited  email addresses' using a server-assigned IP
address.  Those  with  static  addresses  (Demon   Net/Freeserve)
should  use  this  version.  In  fact,  you  should  get a static
address simply to use this version. MoMail17.lha has  been  found
buggy and unusable. I never got around to fixing it.

Mo-Mail is public domain. If you decide to copy it, be my  guest.
Copy  the  entire  code,  do  what  you  want but do NOT make any
attempt to remove/update my version on Aminet/elsewhere. Even  if
you  make  a  near-direct  copy of this - make sure you give it a
name of your own! That's all I ask. Thank you.

@endnode
@node "spec" "Specifications"
Mo-Email is currently running on my:  A1200/020/882
                                      10 Meg RAM
                                      85 Meg Drive
                                      /X version 4.#?
                                      YAM 2.00 Preview 7

Whether this will work on other versions of /X, I have no idea.
Will it work on other systems? Fame/S!x/DayDream? I don't know.
Good answers.

@endnode
@node "Impo" "Important!"
Anyone on the BBS using split names will become hyphenated:

 IE: 'The Count' becomes 'The-Count'

Else they do not have a valid email address.

KILL:
I agonised over this for days. Finally came  up  with  this  lame
idea  for  deleting  mail.  It  deletes all current mail for that
user. They have chances to download etc. It will ask whether  the
user wants to KILL the mail yet (or not). It works just fine  and
I see no reason to update it ever. If a user chooses to  download
the  current-read  message  then  it will be named '07743.001' or
whatever name YAM has assigned to it.

If  the door is in use then no other node can access their email,
having  to  wait until userX is finished. Simultaneous use of YAM
scanning etc could result in hassle. Or so I theorise.

Please read the updates text for more info.

@endnode
