@node "inst" "Getting this sod to work..."
(1) You must make sure that RexxMast/RPStart is running to allow
use of AIM(Rexx) doors in AmiExpress.

(2) Copy all files from archive to where they should be.

(3) Find 'doors:email/email.info' and change tooltypes to suit
    your system:

    DOMAIN=    funky.demon.co.uk etc:)

    FOLDER=    Which folder in YAM you wish to use. If you currently
               have only four folders then add another. YAM will call this
               folder 4 (the first folder is 0). This is where all mail TO
               BBS users is stored. Any mail they write goes to 'outgoing'.

    SIGNATURE= Open your YAM config and go to:
               'signature/default signature'
               Clicking this twice will change it to:
               'Alt signature #2'

               Careful, as signature 0 = no signature, so
               'alt. signature #2' is 4. Okay!

    REGGEDTO=  Your BBS name/whatever

    PREFSFILE= Where your main YAM config is located.
               Usual is - 'YAM:.config'

    MAILDIR=   Where your YAM folders (incoming/outgoing/etc) are
               located. Usual is - 'YAM:'

    ATTACH=    yes or no - Disable/Enable file attach function.

    TIME=      The hour that you will do your mail run. If you set
               it to 22 then that equals 10pm. Therefore
               MoEmail is not avail during 22 and 23 (10pm and 11pm).
               Set to 25 or some other non-time number if you wish
               this function disabled.

(4) Make sure you have the following files in your 'C:' dir:

    C:waitforport
    C:delete

The above MUST be in C: You may  already  have  'waitforport'  in
REXXC but it MUST exist here also.

(5) Check for these in 'LIBS:'

    rexxsyslib.library
    rexxtricks.library
    rexxsupport.library

(6) Add '~CC_MOSEARCH|' to your logon script so users  can  check
for awaiting mail while logging on.

(7)  Try and keep YAM running. If YAM is not present when a user
wants it then the program will load it. Which may bug the fuck.

(8) You as sysop will be in control of  sending/receiving  mail.
Do  this  when  you want. Every day/every other day. Your choice.
There could be a program written  (independant  of  MoMail)  that
will send Miami/YAM online and check for mail.

(9) If you decide to run YAM before running this door then please
make sure your config file etc is the same as the door tooltypes.
@endnode

@node "Upda" "Updates..."
v2.06  -  Mail run time check implemented.
          See tooltypes configuration guide.
          Script to send YAM on a mail will be a separate archive.
          If I write it, that is. It should appear next to this
          archive on Aminet.

v2.05  -  Another big update. This is definately the BETA FINAL.
          It has enough functions.
          But of course, mail me with problems/ideas.

          Alias problem sorted. If...
          'safra@yourbbs.somewhere.co.org'
          ...received a mail addressed to:
          'Safra Coerlin <safra@yourbbs.somewhere.co.org>'
          ...then previously the 'alias (Safra Coerlin)' would have
          made this an unknown email. Safra would not get it.
          Routine changed to remove this bug.

          YAM 'prefsfile' and 'maildir' now added to tooltypes
          in case anyone uses a strange system setup.

          MOSEARCH will not load YAM now. If a user is logging on
          in a hurry, they don't wanna sit there and wait for your YAM
          to load if they don't care about email. Basically, this little
          fix has saved your life/made you friends. Your welcome.

          Abort message routine sorted.

          Notice a linespace between 'Send to:' and 'Subject' when
          writing mail. For some reason, when the two lines are together,
          the letter 'm' appears in the 'subject' input. Two hours to
          fucking spot this thing. Only happened with certain 'Send to:'
          addresses. IE: 'Send to: l@l.com' - strange.

          WriteAttach exists again. Enable/Disable via tooltype.
          Problem of filenames with spaces still exists. Routine to check
          for spaces or '#?.info' files brings up a message explaining
          to the user regarding failure.

          Readmail feature now uses YAM routines. It's a little slower
          but YAM will split headers/attachments/plaintext - which is
          easier for handling.

          Reply feature now quotes original message.

          About screen changed.

          Previous update said no major changes would take place.
          I promised aswell. What can I say?
          'You can say sorry, you bastard.'
          'Sorry.'
          'Man, that was insincere...'

          Anyway, this version can be spread.
          I'm gonna sit back and check this thing through again.
          While waiting for other bug reports.

v2.04  -  File attach removed. Giving me too much shit and I haven't
          the patience to sort it right now:(

          ***MAJOR OVERHAUL*** of entire program:

          First thing you notice is lack of files. Well, I finally
          found a way to address YAM as well as AEREXXCONTROL-etc
          so everything is in one file now, excluding the logon-email
          check rexx.

          ***Basically, ditch old files and re-install***
          ***This won't happen again, I dearly promise***

          ;)

          Tooltypes added for ease. Rexxtricks and Rexxsupport library
          have totally saved this program. Not all of the original C:
          commands are needed now. Go through installation docs again.

          Signature now uses the inbuilt YAM sig creator.

          Other node using MMail/lost carrer users etc all
          reprogrammed.

          All programming texts tidied up.

v2.03  -  File Attach added. This needs some serious testing.
          I've not had any problems, aside from the fact that any
          uploaded file needs to be one word. Split filename will
          result in 'file already exists' but the program will
          carry on happily, not attaching anything.
          Put a file in 'doors:email/' called 'NoAttach' and
          this function will be disabled. Any file. If a user
          uploads multiple files then only the first is used.

          If no mail is there for the user then a different
          message will be displayed.

          Overall: I am very happy with this proggy, even though it
          looks 'tacked together in a day'. Learning more and more about
          Arexx - use of libs etc. I find that 'makedir' 'delete' etc are
          all part of rexxsupport.library. The less 'outside' files I have
          to use, the better.

v2.02  -  MoMail  not  bothered  now  by uppercase/lowercase. The
          email will be read by 'sAFRA' or 'safra'...etc.
          Used rexxtricks.library to achieve this.
          Yes, there was probably an easier way, but.

          Hyphenation of user name if a split word prog routine
          changed. I had some nightmare check routine which has
          been replaced by a built-in Arexx function. Likely there
          are a million more built-in functions that could reduce
          this whole program to ten lines long, damn it.

          Aside from the check for '@' in any entered email address
          also added is the check to make sure there are no spaces.

          Layout changes. New main menu.

          Guide re-written. All UPDATE info now within.

          Filename change to MMail20x.lha
          Old filename was 13 chars long.
          Which is not allowed when upping to an /X board.
          Oh man, a bug in the file name. Sickening.
          I'm sure some god is laughing at me.

          Counter on 'readmail'. 'Message 1 of 3' etc. Cheap.

          'Format SYS:' command implemented via 'ZZ' command on main.
          Then pressed by accident.
          Re-wrote whole program from scratch.

v2.01 - Another rush release. Must stop. No. Make me. Punch. Oh, okay.

v2.00 - Static vers. Rushed release. Shouldn't have. Idiot.

v1.07 - Dyn-vers. ...this on BBS's still. Yikes. Delete!

v1.06 - Dyn-vers. ...and...

v1.05 - Dyn-vers. See this...

v1.04 - Dynamic version. Oh dear me.


@endnode
